The paper proposes a method for learning similarity measures from data, which is a common task in machine learning. The focus is on high-dimensional sparse data, which suggests that the paper could belong to sub-categories related to machine learning on high-dimensional data, such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also mentions classification and dimensionality reduction, which are tasks commonly studied in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper mentions data exploration, which could suggest a connection to sub-categories related to data analysis and visualization, such as cs.CL (Computation and Language).
